        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41104",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mjh_ca",
                        "name": "mjh_ca",
                        "displayName": "Marc Hodgins",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The $object passed to _makeRequest() is expected to already have spaces (and certain other characters) urlencoded.  The _fixupObjectName() method does this.  Public methods that operate on objects call $this->_fixupObjectName($object) prior to _makeRequest().  Marking as not an issue.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mjh_ca",
                        "name": "mjh_ca",
                        "displayName": "Marc Hodgins",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-06-19T11:01:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-06-19T11:01:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41106",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mjh_ca",
                        "name": "mjh_ca",
                        "displayName": "Marc Hodgins",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Although the code you referenced is actually within _makeRequest(), I see your point regarding the public addSignature() method requiring a urlencoded path, while the other public methods which operate on objects do not.  Reopening and will submit a proposed patch in a moment.  The best approach without breaking existing behavior may be to expose _fixupObjectName as a public method and note in the phpdoc for addSignature that the path parameter must be encoded.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mjh_ca",
                        "name": "mjh_ca",
                        "displayName": "Marc Hodgins",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-06-19T12:18:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-06-19T12:18:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/41107",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mjh_ca",
                        "name": "mjh_ca",
                        "displayName": "Marc Hodgins",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Since public method addSignature() needs the path to be specially urlencoded, and protected method _fixupObjectName() already does this internally, this patch changes _fixupObjectName() to be a public method fixupObjectName().\r\n\r\nDeprecates but retains the original protected function as a proxy for BC.  Also adds comment to addSignature() to be clear that usage of addSignature requires running the object path through fixupObjectName() first.\r\n\r\nAlso includes a unit test.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mjh_ca",
                        "name": "mjh_ca",
                        "displayName": "Marc Hodgins",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-06-19T12:43:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-06-19T12:43:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/42869",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think that this problem was fixed by [~Padraic] in ZF-10197 with ZF\\-1.11.\r\nTry\r\n{code}\r\n$config = array(\r\n   'rfc3986_strict' => true\r\n);\r\n$client = new Zend_Http_Client(null, $config);\r\nZend_Service_Amazon_S3::setClient($client);\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-11-07T02:40:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-11-07T02:41:07.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
